
Cloud Engineering Lead:

In this role, you will:

Identify and advocate use-cases for cloud integrations; assist in planning migration of applications and technology services onto the enterprise cloud platform.
Design and oversee proof of concepts by which to objectively measure and optimally exploit various cloud services.
Liaise effectively with project team members, business stakeholders and external vendors to build strong partnerships to help create a collaborative, transparent, and high performing culture.
Support and coach Engineers to develop strong engineering skills including sharing different requirements development techniques such as user story development and human centered design
You’ll need:

Experience working in complex enterprise environments
Deep understanding of Linux and/or Windows systems engineering o Strong experience in one or more of the following public cloud platforms: AWS, Azure, Google Cloud and with a desire to work with many o Experienced with setting up cloud-based CI/CD/CT Pipelines including using tools such as Git, Bamboo/Jenkins, Docker, Kubernetes/OpenShift, SonarCube, etc. o Solid Configuration Management Experience with either Puppet, Chef, Ansible or Saltstack
Engineering and people leadership experience
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
Excellent communication skills both written and verbal

Cloud Engineer:

Build and configure cloud solutions in development, pre-production and production environments
Work with automation tools including develop scripts for automation and
Work with vendors to produce outcomes that are aligned to AustralianSuper standards, design and outcomes.
Prepare detailed designs for the cloud integrations when required
You’ll need:

Experience working in complex enterprise environments
Deep understanding of Linux and/or Windows systems engineering
Strong experience in one or more of the following public cloud platforms: AWS, Azure, Google Cloud and with a desire to work with many
Experienced with setting up cloud-based CI/CD/CT Pipelines.
Solid Configuration Management Experience with either Puppet, Chef, Ansible or Saltstack.
Certification in one or more of the key cloud technologies: Azure, Google, O365, Cloud Security Solutions or Cloud Networking.
